description: A spider has written "Goodbye world" within the intricate structure of its web. Below, it hangs from a single strand of silk, having tied a noose around its neck. The scene presents the morbid absurdity of an animal committing suicide by hanging, a human method, using its own natural material. This literal and dark depiction is ironic, contrasting the spider's web-weaving skill with its ultimate act of self-destruction. The combination of the familiar web and the shocking act creates a surreal image.
